-- China’s Top Planner Sets Up Climate-Change Center, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2012-06-11T14:37:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-11/china-s-top-planner-sets-up-climate-change-center-xinhua-says.html
The National Development and Reform
Commission,  China ’s top economic planning agency, will set up a
research center aimed at facilitating efforts to cope with
climate change, Xinhua News Agency reported.  The National Center for Climate Change Strategy and
International Cooperation will research strategic planning, laws
and regulations, international policy, carbon markets and
informating consulting, Xinhua said, citing Xie Zhenhua, deputy
director of the NDRC.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  